@node "comp"
@title "Compiled Doors"
                               COMPILED DOORS
                              ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
  All doors in this archive are compiled using the RexxPlus Arexx Compiler.

     To get the doors to work on you /X system, you must run RPStart and
       have the libraries included in the archive copied to your LIBS:
  It is advisable to put RPStart in you User-Startup so you won't forget it

   If you would like a copy of the uncompiled sources of the doors included
      in this archive, send 1500 BEF (50 USD) to the author of the doors.
           Cash money (no coins) or EuroCheque in BEF only please.

  This can be a large amount of money, but if you see what money I spend in
   my doors (time, phonecalls) and if you really want the sources to study
                       them, this isn't too much I think...

        The adress where you can send the money to can be found under
                              @{"postcardware" link "post"} button...

Note :

 Compiled doors do not work on all systems (blame the /X RexxPort for this)
                   but the advantage for me is much greater.

  I decided to do this compilation of my doors because I noticed that more
    and more people started using pieces of my doors, or sometimes just
    renaming the door and then releasing it under their own name/group.
            If you want you can buy the sources as staded above.

                                                                    FRaNKy.
@endnode
@node "what"
@title "FRaNKy's Simple Wall V 1.2 - What is it ?"
                                WHAT IS IT ?
                               ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Simple Wall is (as the name says) a wall door for the /X 2.xx and up
                           Bulleting Board Program
@endnode
@node "inst"
@title "FRaNKy's Simple Wall V 1.2 - Installation"
                                INSTALLATION
                               ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   The files SWALL.#? should be placed in the directory "Doors:PTL/SWall/"
          The icon (Wall.info) should be in "BBS:Commands/BBSCMD"

  The add the door to your Logon-sequence by adding '~CC_WALL' to the file
               'NodeX/bull.txt' (where X is the node number)
@endnode
@node "conf"
@title "FRaNKy's Simple Wall V 1.2 - Config File"
                                CONFIGURATION
                               ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
            You must edit the file "Doors:PTL/SWall/Swall.cfg"
                     The file must be edited like this :

       Line 1 : Password needed to access the maintainance menu
       Line 2 : Person who can access the maintainance menu
       Line 3 : Person who can access the maintainance menu
       Line 4 : ....

                             Example :
                             ---------------
                             superimperialstardestroyer
                             da cool one
                             da slave
                             da superslave
                             ---------------
@endnode
