@node "menu"
@title "Simple Wall V 1.2 - Menu Options"
                                MENU OPTIONS
                               ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
       Users who can access the Maintainance will see this menu-line

      Add a line ? [Y]es [N]o [A]nonymous     [M]aintainance [C]redits

              Yes          : The user wants to add a line
              No           : The user don't wants to add a line
              Anonymous    : The user wants to add an anonymous
                             line, the user name and his line
                             will be written to a logfile
              Maintainance : Allows you to do some maintainance
              Credits      : Shows the credits

    Users who can not access the maintainance will not have that option.
    Users in the @{"twitlist" link "twit"} can only select 'No' and 'Credits'
@endnode
@node "maint"
@title "Simple Wall V 1.2 - Maintainance Options"
                            MAINTAINANCE OPTIONS
                           ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
     If you want a user to have access to the Maintainance options,
                 you must put his name in the @{"config-file" link "conf"}

     View Maintainance logfile : Displays the maintainance logfile
     View Anonymous-Logfile    : Diplays the anonymous writers logfile
     Delete Logfile            : Deletes the anonymous writers logfile
     Reset Wall                : Restores the wall to the original
     Edit Wall                 : Allows you to edit a wallline
     Show Wall                 : Displays the wall
     Add user to Twitlist      : Adds a user to the @{"twitlist" link "twit"}
     View Twitlist             : Views the @{"twitlist" link "twit"}
     Go Back                   : Returns to the @{"Main menu" link "menu"}
@endnode


@node "hist"
@title "FRaNKy's Simple Wall V 1.2 - History"
                                    HISTORY
                                   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

                  ... - 0.9 : Internal Beta Releases
                        1.0 : First Worldwide Release
                        1.1 : - Sysop does not have to be in the cfg-file
                                anymore to have acces to the maintenance
                              - You can now edit the wall
                              - You stay in the maintainance menu untill
                                you press <ENTER>
                              - Added a second logo
                              - Interal source updates
                        1.2 : - Added ANSI-animation for fast connects
                              - Improved the centering of the wall-line
                              - Added a Maintainance-Logile
                              - Deletion of Logfiles and Wall-Reset
                                now asks for a confirmation
                              - Added a @{"Twitlist" link "twit"}
                              - Everyone can access the maintainance menu
                                now as long as he is in the @{"cfg-file" link "conf"} and
                                knows the password
@endnode
@node "twit"
@title ""FRaNKy's Simple Wall V 1.2 - The Twitlist"
                                     TWITLIST
                                    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
If, for some reason, you don't want a certain user to write on the wall,
add his name to the twitlist (you can do this from @{"maintainance" link "maint"}).

The name is case-insensitive but the name has to be exactly the same for
all other ASCII-chars (example : user^bla - don't forget the ^)
@endnode
@node "stor"
@title "FRaNKy's Simple Wall V 1.2 - The Story Off"
                                 THE STORY OFF
                                ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
This door is currently the most developed I ever made (untill Piss-O-Rama
will be updated that is).

I started this door because I wanted a wall where I could write anonymously
on but didn't find one...

Once the mail wall was finished the shell around went quickly so I guess
that coding the wall to an 1.0 took me about 3-4 days.  Again I changed
the config-file 2 times but in this way I really like it so it'll stay
this way.
@endnode
